The paper proposes a deep learning approach for object detection and affordance detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a multi-task loss function, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results and performance metrics, which are often discussed in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
